docs.abstract: All the major battles for equal rights — racial, ethnic, gender, sexual orientation, disability — are explored in “The Good Fight.”
docs.snippet: All the major battles for equal rights — racial, ethnic, gender, sexual orientation, disability — are explored in “The Good Fight.”
docs.lead_paragraph: The 54-mile march for voting rights from Selma to Alabama’s state capital, Montgomery, took more than good legs and sturdy shoes. It took defying the police, who ambushed hundreds of men, women and children — on a bridge named for a Klu Klux Klan leader — and beat them bloody. It took a court order and it took journalists covering the struggles to tell and shock the world.

headline.main: A Look at the Heart-Wrenching Moments From Equal Rights Battles

docs.abstract: In Jackson, Miss., the president hailed heroes of the civil rights movement even as activists and politicians said his presence insulted the effort to confront the state’s history.
docs.snippet: In Jackson, Miss., the president hailed heroes of the civil rights movement even as activists and politicians said his presence insulted the effort to confront the state’s history.
docs.lead_paragraph: JACKSON, Miss. — President Trump’s presence jolted the opening of a civil rights museum here on Saturday, generating boycotts from some leaders in the movement and small protests by activists as the state’s attempt to confront its racially violent past clashed with more recent divisions wrought by Mr. Trump’s presidency.

headline.main: Trump, Rejecting Calls to Stay Away, Speaks at Civil Rights Museum
headline.print_headline: Trump, Rejecting Calls  To Stay Away, Speaks At Civil Rights Museum

docs.abstract: In “Women & Power: A Manifesto,” the Cambridge classicist Mary Beard describes the scale of the problem and suggests some exciting remedies.
docs.snippet: In “Women & Power: A Manifesto,” the Cambridge classicist Mary Beard describes the scale of the problem and suggests some exciting remedies.
docs.lead_paragraph: According to Aristotle, women’s voices were proof of their wickedness. Virtue expressed itself in deep, full-throated sounds — the noise of the lion, the bull and (no surprise here) the human male. Women’s speech, however, its pitch and prattle, was considered dangerous, even unsanitary. The very sound of their voices, it was believed, could sink the state.

headline.main: From Ancient Myths to Modern Day, Women and the Struggle for Power

docs.abstract: John Schnatter will be replaced in January by the company’s chief operating officer. In November, Mr. Schnatter blamed a decline in sales on national anthem protests.

docs.lead_paragraph: The pizza franchise Papa John’s announced Thursday that its chief executive, who recently blamed the National Football League’s handling of the national anthem controversy for the company’s declining sales, will step down from the position at the end of the month.

headline.main: Papa John’s Chief Executive to Step Down, Weeks After Blaming N.F.L. for Sales Slump
